  "text": "A number of methods described in the literature using more advanced SPE have grown considerably [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] because of their better repeatability, lower solvent consumption and reduced time for sample pre-treatment. SPE is the process with proper purification and concentration effects with satisfactory recovery. In addition, an immunoassay SPE method was reported as a possibility of extraction of alphaamanitin from serum [CITATION_4] . Described method achieved medium extraction efficiency of 61% and required long-time immunoaffinity column preparation.",
